<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer8494743786029849643">Robert McCrum is an associate editor of the Observer. He was born and educated in Cambridge. For nearly 20 years he was editor-in-chief of the publishers Faber &amp; Faber. He is the co-author of The Story of English (1986), and has written six novels. He was the literary editor of the Observer from 1996 to 2008, and has been a regular contributor to the Guardian since 1990<br/></span>

</div>
</div>

